snippet.title: Gates grant to fund testicle-blasting contraceptive
snippet.description: Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation gives $100,000 grant to researchers investigating the use of ultrasound as a reversible male contraceptive.

snippet.title: Tamron sets price for 150-600mm supertele: $1,069
snippet.description: The third-party lensmaker's new supertelephoto won't cost much more than an earlier 200-500mm model with no image stabilization.

snippet.title: Gates Foundation offers $100k for 'next-gen condom'
snippet.description: The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation believes that if condoms actually felt better to use, global health could improve substantially.

snippet.title: Research makes case for home blood pressure monitoring
snippet.description: A lot of people have normal readings at doctors' offices, but elevated blood pressure at work or home. Home blood pressure monitoring can help identify these people, studies show.

snippet.title: Incase Sonic Headphones
snippet.description: The Incase Sonic headphones are a standout first effort for Incase. Their elongated earcups and memory foam lend a supremely comfortable fit, and the powerful titanium drivers inside add sweetness to their sound that earns them a universal recommendation for all types of music fans.

snippet.title: Nanoribbons let beating hearts power their own pacemakers
snippet.description: Researchers show that materials called piezoelectrics, packaged onto flexible strips attached to animal hearts, can supply power for medical devices where batteries pose problems.

snippet.title: Sennheiser HD 700 headphones: Not for the faint of heart
snippet.description: Sennheiser announced at CES 2012 the HD 700 high-end premium headphones designed for those who want the best audio quality.

snippet.title: Bowers & Wilkins P7
snippet.description: The company's new flagship model, the $400 P7, has an over-the-ear design and offers richer, more detailed sound with deep bass.

snippet.title: Will technology ever deliver a perfect speaker or headphone?
snippet.description: Aside from a handful of audiophiles, no one really wants that -- even if it were compact and affordable. Everyone just wants a sound that sounds good to them.

snippet.title: JBL's ultimate speaker: Everest DD66000
snippet.description: The Audiophiliac auditions JBL's best speaker, and it's really, really good.
